{
    "name": "Plagued Horse",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or herd (3\u201330)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Disease (Ex)</b> Demon Plague: Bite\u2014injury; <i>save</i> Fortitude DC 13; <i>onset</i> 1 day; <i>frequency</i> 1/day; <i>effect</i> 1d3 Constitution damage and 1d6 Wisdom damage, victim is fatigued if it takes any ability damage from the disease, and certain creatures slain by demon plague rise as plagued beasts; <i>cure</i> 3 consecutive saves."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "When animals are stricken with demon plague, they may arise as undead and further spread the disease. Some demons and cultists are fond of using plagued horses as mounts."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>The rotting skeleton and muscles of this fanged, decaying horse seem barely able to hold together.</i>",
